{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Button group · Stisla v3{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Button group</h1>
    <p class="lead">A row of buttons that share chrome so they read as a single control.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic</h2>
    <p>Wrap two or more <code>.btn</code>s in <code>.btn-group</code> with <code>role="group"</code> and an <code>aria-label</code>. Outer corners round, inner corners square, adjacent borders dedupe into a single seam.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Basic example">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary">Left</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary">Middle</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary">Right</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Outline</h2>
    <p>Outline members work the same way — adjacent borders dedupe at the seam.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Outline example">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Left</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Middle</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Right</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Mixed</h2>
    <p>A loud action paired with a quiet alternative. Same pattern as the standalone primary plus outline-neutral pairing, locked together as one chip.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Mixed example">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary">Publish</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Save draft</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sizes</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.btn-group--sm</code> or <code>.btn-group--lg</code> on the wrapper. The modifier retunes child <code>--btn-*</code> vars so every member shrinks or grows at once, matching the standalone <code>.btn--sm</code> / <code>.btn--lg</code> cadence (28 / 36 / 44 px under default density).</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: flex-start;">
      <div class="btn-group btn-group--sm" role="group" aria-label="Small">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Left</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Middle</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Right</button>
      </div>
      <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Default">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Left</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Middle</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Right</button>
      </div>
      <div class="btn-group btn-group--lg" role="group" aria-label="Large">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Left</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Middle</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">Right</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Toggle group</h2>
    <p>Members that flip on and off carry <code>aria-pressed="true|false"</code>. The base <code>.btn</code> reads <code>aria-pressed</code> and paints the active state. Click handling lands with the JS contract in a later step; the markup below is hardcoded for the visual.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Text style">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" aria-pressed="true" aria-label="Bold">
        <i data-lucide="bold"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" aria-pressed="false" aria-label="Italic">
        <i data-lucide="italic"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" aria-pressed="true" aria-label="Underline">
        <i data-lucide="underline"></i>
      </button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Tabs / segmented control</h2>
    <p>Use a <code>role="tablist"</code> wrapper and mark the current member with <code>data-state="active"</code> + <code>aria-selected="true"</code>. The base <code>.btn</code> reads <code>data-state="active"</code> and paints the active member — same hook the sidebar, list-group, table and pagination use. Roving-tabindex keyboard navigation lands with the JS contract.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="btn-group" role="tablist" aria-label="Calendar view">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" role="tab" data-state="active" aria-selected="true">Day</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Week</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" role="tab" aria-selected="false">Month</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Checkbox &amp; radio</h2>
    <p><code>.btn-check</code> visually hides a native <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> so the paired <code>&lt;label class="btn"&gt;</code> carries the visible shape. <code>:checked</code> forwards the active paint to the label via the same selector chain <code>.btn</code> uses for <code>aria-pressed</code>; native semantics drive state. Multiple members can stay active for checkboxes.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Format">
      <input type="checkbox" class="btn-check" id="bg-check-1" autocomplete="off" checked>
      <label class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" for="bg-check-1">Bold</label>
      <input type="checkbox" class="btn-check" id="bg-check-2" autocomplete="off">
      <label class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" for="bg-check-2">Italic</label>
      <input type="checkbox" class="btn-check" id="bg-check-3" autocomplete="off">
      <label class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" for="bg-check-3">Underline</label>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
    <p>Radios work the same way; only one member can be active at a time.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Alignment">
      <input type="radio" class="btn-check" name="bg-radio" id="bg-radio-1" autocomplete="off" checked>
      <label class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" for="bg-radio-1">Left</label>
      <input type="radio" class="btn-check" name="bg-radio" id="bg-radio-2" autocomplete="off">
      <label class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" for="bg-radio-2">Center</label>
      <input type="radio" class="btn-check" name="bg-radio" id="bg-radio-3" autocomplete="off">
      <label class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral" for="bg-radio-3">Right</label>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>With icons</h2>
    <p>Icons compose the same as in standalone buttons. <code>.btn--icon-only</code> gives a square slot.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Format">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral btn--icon-only" aria-label="Bold">
        <i data-lucide="bold"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral btn--icon-only" aria-label="Italic">
        <i data-lucide="italic"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral btn--icon-only" aria-label="Underline">
        <i data-lucide="underline"></i>
      </button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Split button</h2>
    <p>Pair a primary action with a caret-only trigger. The trigger reuses <code>.btn--icon-only</code> with a chevron, so no split-specific class ships. Dropdown attach behavior lands with the Dropdown component in a later step.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Save">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary">Save</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary btn--icon-only" aria-label="More save options" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false">
        <i data-lucide="chevron-down"></i>
      </button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Vertical</h2>
    <p>Swap <code>.btn-group</code> for <code>.btn-group--vertical</code> to stack the members. Outer corners round on the top and bottom instead of left and right.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="btn-group--vertical" role="group" aria-label="Vertical example">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary">Top</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary">Middle</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary">Bottom</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Toolbar</h2>
    <p>Combine multiple groups under <code>.btn-toolbar</code>. The toolbar carries a default <code>0.5rem</code> gap between groups so they breathe without inline utility classes.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="btn-toolbar" role="toolbar" aria-label="Toolbar with button groups">
      <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="First group">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">1</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">2</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">3</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">4</button>
      </div>
      <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Second group">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">5</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">6</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">7</button>
      </div>
      <div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Third group">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--outline btn--neutral">8</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Customization</h2>
    <p>Two variables retune <code>.btn-group</code> + <code>.btn-toolbar</code>. Sizes retune the child <code>--btn-*</code> vars in modifier scope rather than introducing per-size vars on the group — same model as <code>.btn--sm</code> / <code>.btn--lg</code>. Override on the wrapper, a parent scope, or <code>:root</code>; the cascade scopes the change.</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Variable</th>
            <th>Default</th>
            <th>Use</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--btn-group-radius</code></td>
            <td>var(--st-btn-radius, var(--st-radius))</td>
            <td>Outer corner radius. Inner corners stay square. <code>--sm</code> / <code>--lg</code> retune this in modifier scope.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--btn-toolbar-gap</code></td>
            <td>0.5rem</td>
            <td>Space between groups inside a <code>.btn-toolbar</code>.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p>The group's chrome — members' borders, fills, hover and active paint — lives on the child <code>.btn</code>. To recolor a tabset or toggle group, set <code>--btn-bg</code> / <code>--btn-tone</code> on the members, not on the wrapper. See the <a class="link" href="/buttons">buttons</a> page for the full <code>.btn</code> variable surface.</p>
  </section>
{% endblock %}
